1
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:34,576
There's a perfectly good staircase,
and no one ever uses it.

2
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:38,455
It's been a while
since you've set foot on this seabed.

3
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:40,957
The troublemaker of the Great Hall.

4
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:44,294
That was a long time ago, Alaira.

5
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:45,920
Was it though?

6
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:49,424
I hear you've stirred up trouble again.

7
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:53,511
Word is, you've taken on a new apprentice.

8
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:55,138
You know already?

9
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:56,890
Word travels fast.

10
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:59,559
I mean, they might be tied, right?

11
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:02,062
To the "Brimmed Caps"?

12
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:06,941
It's been four years
since forbidden magic was used.

13
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:08,526
She's an important lead.

14
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:11,321
That's not why.

15
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:16,326
She hasn't taken the exam yet,
so she isn't officially my apprentice.

16
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:18,203
What? Not yet?

17
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:19,954
It's too soon.

18
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:21,456
And the timing's bad.

19
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,291
Oh, that's right.

20
00:01:23,374 --> 00:01:26,211
This time of year, the Dadah Range
where exams are held…

21
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:29,214
Is at its highest elevation.

22
00:01:29,297 --> 00:01:31,716
I can't send her out there now.

23
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:34,260
Her life would be at risk.

24
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,992
Hey, Agott?

25
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:25,288
Are we really doing this?
The master isn't even here.

26
00:03:25,371 --> 00:03:26,664
THE TRIAL AT DADAH RANGE

27
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:28,875
You test alone no matter when you do it.

28
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:31,794
But I just got here.

29
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:34,756
I passed when I was ten.

30
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:37,217
Everyone takes it to become an apprentice.

31
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,635
The conditions never change.

32
00:03:39,135 --> 00:03:40,136
I see.

33
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:44,432
The first test is the
"Consent of the Crown."

34
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:48,645
You can only bring
three magical contraptions and materials.

35
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:52,941
You have to reach the peak
of Dadah Range without anyone's help

36
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:56,319
and bring back the diadem herb
that grows there.

37
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:59,864
The guidance orb that shows the way
to any destination,

38
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,824
and the vapor bubble for drinking water.

39
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:04,827
That's probably all you can manage.

40
00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:08,248
Now go.

41
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:13,962
Oh, and, um…

42
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,215
Do you have any shoes?

43
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:20,718
- Shoes?
- Those shoes are contraptions too, right?

44
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:23,346
I saw the soles glowing

45
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:25,723
when you and Master Qifrey
were flying around.

46
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:30,228
So, if you don't mind, those shoes,

47
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:34,148
maybe you can lend them to me?

48
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:36,985
That's too much to ask! I'm sorry!

49
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:38,861
Forget I asked!

50
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:46,577
I'll lend them to you.

51
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:49,497
- Just hurry up.
- Thanks…

52
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:51,541
And go!

53
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:54,961
I forgot to tell you,

54
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:57,922
but you can only take the test once.

55
00:04:58,006 --> 00:04:59,424
If you fail,

56
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:02,635
you can't be approved as
Master Qifrey's apprentice.

57
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:04,679
You'll have to leave the atelier.

58
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,483
I suddenly feel so alone,

59
00:05:18,526 --> 00:05:20,361
but I've got to do my best!

60
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:22,363
There's no turning back.

61
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:27,618
I wonder how you use the guidance orb.

62
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:40,590
It must be telling me to go this way.

63
00:05:43,384 --> 00:05:44,510
Okay!

64
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:47,180
It's just hiking. No big deal.

65
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,935
I can do it!

66
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:56,105
Agott said she passed

67
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,649
when she was ten!

68
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:04,572
If she did it at ten…

69
00:06:08,659 --> 00:06:11,662
I'm sure it's a piece of cake!

70
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:20,838
No way.

71
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:23,591
Don't tell me…

72
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:34,852
That's Dadah Range?

73
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:43,194
The guidance orb is pointing up.

74
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:45,071
So it must be there.

75
00:06:49,951 --> 00:06:52,537
I never thought it'd be floating
in the sky.

76
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:01,045
Ta-da!

77
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,381
The shoes I borrowed from Agott!

78
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:05,425
Hup!

79
00:07:18,896 --> 00:07:22,859
The seal is split with half on each foot.

80
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:32,285
Make sure they don't shift.

81
00:07:32,368 --> 00:07:34,036
Align them perfectly…

82
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:45,590
Wow! I'm really floating!

83
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:55,683
It's like Master Qifrey said.

84
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,519
I'm like a newborn foal.

85
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:03,357
But…

86
00:08:07,945 --> 00:08:09,280
I flew.

87
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:15,203
If I can fly,
I'll be at the top in no time.

88
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:17,705
All right!

89
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:19,624
I'll give it my best!

90
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:27,840
You'll get used to it soon
and be running around in no time.

91
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:32,386
I'll get used to it soon…

92
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:59,038
- Here's the application form. Thanks.
- Of course.

93
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:02,166
- Totorei, number 12.
- Yes.

94
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:06,629
If you lived in the Hall,
you wouldn't have to travel for this.

95
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:08,548
You can bring your apprentice.

96
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:11,300
The Great Hall is the witches' stronghold.

97
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:13,803
It has everything you need.

98
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:17,098
Then I'll just come when I need to.

99
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:19,559
I've brought it here.

100
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:20,560
Thanks.

101
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:23,813
Your disdain for the Great Hall runs deep.

102
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,566
Keep a close eye on your apprentices.

103
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:28,818
Kids of that age,

104
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:32,738
you never know what they'll get up to
with no adults around.

105
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:36,784
Whoa, easy!

106
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:41,080
My balance has gotten much better.

107
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:44,000
I think I can go a little higher.

108
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,584
A brushbuddy!

109
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:28,085
I've never seen one before!

110
00:10:41,223 --> 00:10:43,684
The shoes are all muddy.

111
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:56,906
Oh no! The seal's rubbed off!

112
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:58,908
No! Is it because I wiped it?!

113
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:00,534
Oh no, no, no!

114
00:11:00,618 --> 00:11:02,912
I know! I'll draw over it!

115
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:08,918
The ink all spilled.

116
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:15,466
What should I do?

117
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:19,679
Maybe it's over for me.

118
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:25,309
Huh? Hey, Agott, have you seen Coco?

119
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:27,812
It's almost time for dinner.

120
00:11:27,895 --> 00:11:29,980
Coco's not here.

121
00:11:30,064 --> 00:11:32,316
She's at Dadah Range for the test.

122
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,901
What?! Alone?

123
00:11:33,984 --> 00:11:36,237
But she just got here!

124
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,321
You didn't stop her?

125
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,823
Hey, Agott!

126
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:41,575
You normally take the test
before you come.

127
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:44,328
That's true, but…

128
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:47,957
If she can't even pass such a simple test,

129
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,835
she shouldn't be an apprentice.

130
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:52,545
You know,

131
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:56,298
I hate people who can't do what I can do.

132
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,634
I gain nothing being with them.

133
00:11:59,301 --> 00:12:02,179
And an outsider at that.

134
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:06,934
Don't worry.
She'll be back without even trying.

135
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:12,648
This time of year, the Dadah Range
floats higher than ever.

136
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:16,277
Not even my sylph shoes can fly that high.

137
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:19,947
She doesn't even know the rules,
has no sense of danger.

138
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:25,119
I don't want an outsider like that
in our world.

139
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:31,375
You're not going to eat, Tetia?

140
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:34,462
I will,

141
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:38,090
but I don't know,
I just have this heavy feeling.

142
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:43,637
Seconds for me.

143
00:12:44,138 --> 00:12:47,349
Am I the only one worried? Sheesh!

144
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:51,353
Either way,
we can only wait for Master Qifrey.

145
00:12:57,401 --> 00:12:59,570
Up! Go!

146
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:00,613
Whoa…

147
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:02,823
Nope!

148
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:06,035
I tried using the little ink I had left,

149
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:08,704
but I can't even lift off anymore.

150
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:12,833
They're so soaked, it just smears.

151
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:23,594
What if I draw
directly on the soles of my feet?

152
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:37,942
No, I can't! Drawing magic
directly on the body is forbidden.

153
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:44,156
I don't know what kind of magic
to use right now.

154
00:13:49,286 --> 00:13:51,622
Agott was right.

155
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:03,259
Wow!

156
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:06,262
Anyone can draw magic,

157
00:14:06,762 --> 00:14:09,056
but not everyone can draw it well.

158
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:14,645
Maybe only people with special talent
can become witches after all.

159
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:24,530
Everyone has been drawing magic

160
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:27,116
since they were little.

161
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:30,077
What could I possibly do?

162
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:44,008
Here.

163
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:51,390
That's right. Straight.

164
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,310
Whoops!

165
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:57,563
Up we go.

166
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:01,317
Hey! Come here!

167
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:08,198
Wow.

168
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:11,160
I had no idea this village
had such a wonderful artisan.

169
00:15:13,245 --> 00:15:14,538
This is magic.

170
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:20,169
I do.

171
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:27,593
I have it! My own magic!

172
00:15:49,823 --> 00:15:52,451
If I moisten it a bit in the water…

173
00:15:58,123 --> 00:16:01,251
My cloak that was wet
is now stiff from the dried mud.

174
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:02,920
I think I can draw with this.

175
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:33,450
It's normal to be a little unsteady
with a new tool.

176
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:40,249
Then I'll just change it
to a tool I'm used to.

177
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:45,713
My fingertips will be able to move freely.

178
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:48,173
Freely…

179
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:57,808
Okay.

180
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:01,812
Good morning, Brushbuddy.
You're not very cautious, are you?

181
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:05,399
It's not the prettiest seal.

182
00:17:05,941 --> 00:17:07,359
A properly drawn one would have

183
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:10,571
a sigil in the center
evenly surrounded by signs.

184
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:15,576
But I also learned that uneven signs
can create too much force.

185
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:18,829
So I tried making
just one really long one.

186
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:21,665
I don't know if it'll work though.

187
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:31,800
You're coming with me?

188
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:36,055
Okay, then be sure to hang on tight!

189
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:38,432
I'm going to close the seal!

190
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:49,359
What? Why?!

191
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:52,029
Did I get the direction of the sign wrong?

192
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:26,939
It worked!

193
00:18:27,022 --> 00:18:30,192
I'm flying with my very own magic!

194
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:32,694
A real flying coat!

195
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:34,446
It's a dream come true.

196
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:49,211
The things I learned helping Mom

197
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:51,255
helped me with my magic.

198
00:18:51,755 --> 00:18:53,090
I never would've imagined.

199
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:57,928
The diadem herb is up higher.

200
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:13,485
The diadem herb!

201
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:14,379
Mom…

202
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:23,722
Wait for me, Mom!

203
00:20:24,973 --> 00:20:27,059
I'll take responsibility for what I did.

204
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:28,727
I promise!

205
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:36,401
What?! So Coco went to Dadah Range
alone to take the test?

206
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:37,903
Yes! Yes, yes!

207
00:20:37,986 --> 00:20:41,281
It's too dangerous!
We have to stop her now!

208
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:43,408
But if we stop her, won't she fail?

209
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:45,911
It's too soon for her
to take the test in any case.

210
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:50,165
She's not like us who grew up with magic.

211
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,918
If something were to happen to Coco…

212
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:56,046
It's not only the girl that'll be lost.

213
00:20:56,129 --> 00:20:57,381
All right.

214
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:04,388
Huh?

215
00:21:04,888 --> 00:21:06,098
- Coco!
- Coco!

216
00:21:06,598 --> 00:21:08,058
Thank goodness!

217
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:10,686
Coco! You're okay!

218
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:14,064
We were so worried about you!

219
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:16,733
Agott!

220
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:20,696
I got the "Consent of the Crown."

221
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:26,326
Have I proved myself?

222
00:21:36,628 --> 00:21:37,546
Coco.

223
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:40,757
Using magic recklessly
without preparation

224
00:21:40,841 --> 00:21:43,802
or basic knowledge is extremely dangerous.

225
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:45,887
You should already know that.

226
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:51,435
A single misstep could have been fatal.

227
00:21:51,935 --> 00:21:53,729
Don't ever do this again.

228
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:56,982
I'm sorry, Master Qifrey.

229
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:02,988
And besides, there's no need
to brave danger to prove yourself.

230
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:05,991
You're already my apprentice.

231
00:22:20,130 --> 00:22:21,506
This is…

232
00:22:25,844 --> 00:22:28,263
It's proof you're a witch.

233
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:30,515
A source of pride,

234
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:35,604
and a restraint you wear on your head
to keep you from abusing magic.

235
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:47,616
As long as you wear it,

236
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:49,743
don't forget its weight.

237
00:22:51,453 --> 00:22:54,956
The witch hat will always
be watching over your magic.

238
00:22:57,626 --> 00:22:59,002
Take good care of it.

239
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:01,505
I will!

240
00:23:02,464 --> 00:23:04,925
Good. Then shall we head back up?

241
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:05,926
Yes.

242
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:12,265
First, dinner!

243
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,060
You should also take a bath.

244
00:23:21,691 --> 00:23:24,486
Subtitle translation by: Emily Noguchi

245
00:23:33,412 --> 00:23:35,163
The seed has sprouted.

246
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:40,919
EPISODE 4: AN ENCOUNTER IN KALHN
